OL,3,C1 in 7 adults in Wales cut spending to
OL,4,Cafford rent or mortgage bill
OL,6,FResearch has revealed that one in
OL,7,Fseven adults in Wales has made cuts to
OL,8,Ftheir spending to be able to afford
OL,9,Ftheir rent or mortgage payments.
OL,11,FShelter Cymru said rent in Wales is
OL,12,Frising faster than anywhere else in
OL,13,Fthe UK, with many people at
OL,14,Fsignificant risk of homelessness.
OL,16,FIt found almost half of private
OL,17,Frenters expect to have to cut spending
OL,18,Fto continue to afford their rent in
OL,19,Fthe future.
