OL,3,C1 in 7 adults in Wales cut spending to
OL,4,Cafford rent or mortgage bill
OL,6,FWelsh Government figures show that in
OL,7,F2024/25, the most common reason for
OL,8,Fpeople to seek support from their
OL,9,Flocal council when threatened with
OL,10,Fhomelessness was the loss of rented or
OL,11,Ftied accommodation.
OL,13,FIn a statement, the Welsh Government
OL,14,Fsaid: "We recognise the very real
OL,15,Fpressures families across Wales are
OL,16,Ffacing with housing costs, and we work
OL,17,Fclosely with partners like Shelter
OL,18,FCymru to support people experiencing
OL,19,Fhousing insecurity.
